search::addField()

Description
    public void search::addField(array $attPairs)
    Adds an element, $attPairs, to the class array, $this->fields

Parameters
    attPairs
    An array containing a name/value pair.

Examples
    <?
	$s = new search($engine);

	$field = array();
	$data  = array();
	$data['table']  = $engine->dbTables("traditionalReserves");
	$data['field']  = "ID";
	$field['value']     = $data;
	$field['fieldName'] = "traditionalReservesID";
	$s->addField($field);
	unset($field);
	unset($data);
	?>
